This repository is a Roblox game framework for shipping many games (genre per game).

Layers:

- **core** = base libraries (Packages, ServerPackages — Knit, Fusion, Wally, ProfileStore)
- **framework** = common engine (src/framework: client, server, shared, ui)
- **games** = per-game code (src/games/<genre>: server, client, shared per genre)

Project structure (filesystem → Roblox):

Packages → ReplicatedStorage/Packages
ServerPackages → ServerScriptService/ServerPackages

src/framework/shared → ReplicatedStorage/FrameworkShared
src/games/<game>/shared → ReplicatedStorage/<game>/Shared

src/framework/server → ServerScriptService/FrameworkServer
src/games/<game>/server → ServerScriptService/<game>/Server

src/framework/client → StarterPlayer/StarterPlayerScripts/Framework
src/games/<game>/client → StarterPlayer/StarterPlayerScripts/<game>/Client

src/framework/ui → StarterGui/MainGui

Which game is synced is determined by the Rojo project file (default = obby; use tycoon.project.json, simulator.project.json, tower-defense.project.json for other games).


Architecture rules:

Framework (src/framework):
- shared: modules, utils, types used by both client and server
- server: Knit Services, systems, managers; entry = bootstrap.server.luau (loads Framework + Game services)
- client: Knit Controllers, utils; entry = bootstrap.client.luau (loads Framework + Game controllers)
- ui: Fusion UI (bootstrap, App, components, screens)

Games (src/games/<genre>):
- shared: config, modules used only by that game
- server: services/, systems/ (Knit services go in services; plain modules in systems)
- client: controllers/ (Knit controllers only)


Knit conventions:

- Services live in framework/server/services/ or games/<game>/server/services/
- Controllers live in framework/client/controllers/ or games/<game>/client/controllers/
- Init scripts load FrameworkServer + any <game>/Server services, and Framework + any <game>/Client controllers (game = obby, tycoon, simulator, tower-defense, etc.)


Shared require paths:

- Framework shared: ReplicatedStorage.FrameworkShared.modules / .utils / .types
- Game shared: ReplicatedStorage.<game>.Shared.config / etc. (e.g. ReplicatedStorage.obby.Shared)


Coding rules:

- All modules must return a table
- Avoid global variables
- Prefer dependency injection
- Use Promise for async flows
- Use Signal for events
- Use Trove for cleanup
- Client-callable Service methods: always validate player and parameters on the server; never trust client input alone
- Event connections (Remote, Bindable): add to Trove so they are disconnected on cleanup


When generating new code:

- Respect the Rojo folder mapping
- Put framework-agnostic code in src/framework; game-specific code in src/games/<genre>
- Follow the Knit architecture
